Package: buddy
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         buddy-bridge (>= ${source:Version}),
         buddy-ws (>= ${source:Version}),
         buddy-system (>= ${source:Version}),
Recommends: buddy-storaged (>= ${source:Version}),
            buddy-networkmanager (>= ${source:Version}),
            buddy-packagekit (>= ${source:Version}),
Suggests: buddy-doc (>= ${source:Version}),
          buddy-pcp (>= ${source:Version}),
          buddy-sosreport (>= ${source:Version}),
          xdg-utils,
Description: Web Console for Linux servers
 The Buddy Web Console enables users to administer GNU/Linux servers using a
 web browser.
 .
 It offers network configuration, log inspection, diagnostic reports, SELinux
 troubleshooting, interactive command-line sessions, and more.

Package: buddy-bridge
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         ${shlibs:Depends},
         glib-networking
Provides: buddy-ssh
Breaks: buddy-ws (<< 181.x),
Replaces: buddy-dashboard (<< 170.x), buddy-ws (<< 181.x)
Description: Buddy bridge server-side component
 The Buddy bridge component installed server side and runs commands on
 the system on behalf of the web based user interface.

Package: buddy-doc
Section: doc
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Buddy deployment and developer guide
 The Buddy Deployment and Developer Guide shows sysadmins how to deploy
 Buddy on their machines as well as helps developers who want to embed
 or extend Buddy.

